title: Watch: Kenneth Acker's leaping interception (video)
text:
Kenneth Acker is rapidly becoming one of the best young cornerbacks in the NFL.
The San Francisco 49ers second-year player and former Grant High Generals star displayed his athletic skills with a leaping interception during the 49ers 20-3 loss to Seattle Thursday night.
Watch
Dangerous throw by DangeRuss. Kenneth Acker makes him pay. #SEAvsSF #TNF https://t.co/h6nHJTm6AS
â€” NFL (@NFL) October 23, 2015
Acker's interception is his second in his last two games and he has three interceptions this season, tied for second in the NFL. While he is officially a second-year player, this is his first year of action after sitting out the 2014 season with a foot injury.
Acker has been burned more than once this season, but he is showing the smarts and skills of a player who has potentially entrenched himself as the 49ers cornerback for many years.
-- Geoffrey C. Arnold | @geoffreyCarnold
